text: Alf Handrahan (born December 27, 1949) is a Canadian retired professional ice hockey player. He played in the World Hockey Association. He played fourteen games for the Cincinnati Stingers. He was born in Alberton, Prince Edward Island. == References == * Category:1949 births Category:Canadian ice hockey right wingers Category:Ice hockey people from Prince Edward Island Category:World Hockey Association players Category:Living people
